@node History

   2.0  - Mostly rewritten and changed internal data structure; now
          it is easier to add new features;
        - fixed enforcer-hits when launcing programs;
        - now it is possible to define the stdout  for a command; 
        - stack size read from command's icon  if it exists;
        - MT can be started from the project icon of a config.-file;
        - no more memory leak when closing an asl.requester  without
          choosing something;
        - characters<32 ASCII in config. file are changed in spaces;
        - doc in Amigaguide format.

   1.6  not released - minor bugs fixed

   1.5  Fixed a strange bug  (it not appears on my A1200;  I've found
        it trying MT on a A4000): if an item is chosen but no icon is
        selected, a wrong string is passed as parameter;
        now you can use %f to choose a file or a directory  using the
        asl filerequester.

   1.4  It's possible to specify the configuration file  using a file
        requester or passing it using ToolTypes;
        fixed a bug (if the given configuration file was without data
        MT didn't clean the menu).

   1.3  It is possible to reconfigure the menu using the asl.requester
        to choose a data file.

   1.2  Item "quit MoreTools" is now optional;
        it is possible to quit also using the "break" DOS command.

   1.1  Added the possibility  to pass  the configuration-file name as
        parameter.

@endnode


@node Future

    The last release of MT was v 1.5 - july 1997:  in a whole year I
  didn't find the time to emprove this program, so I can't assure to
  find time to do it in future.However i'd like to add some features
  like:

  - ability to add/delete/modify a menu without restarting MT;
  - more flexibility in launching programs;
  - running programs according to the type of the selected file (for
    the moment I suggest you to use @{"MultiDisplay" link Multidisplay});
  - ability to read and use tooltypes to launch a program.

    Remarks and suggestions are welcome, of course.

    Remember: the best way to make  a lazy programmer working is let
  him know that there is someone, somewhere in the world,  using his
  proggy. B-)
 
@endnode


@node MultiDisplay

    MultiDisplay  is a program  made  by Fabrice  Colin:  it is very 
  useful if used together with MT.  It is able  to recognize several
  type of files and to call the appropriated program to show it. For
  example, adding this menu item:

  ITEM     view
  COMMAND  workbench:utilities/MultiDisplay "%s"
  OUTPUT   DEFAULT

  you will be able to launch the right program for the selected file
  (text-viewer for texts, editor for sources, MultiView for pics...)
  using only one menu item.

    You can find MD on Aminet:  util/wb/md1_8.lha

    Don't forget to write to the author if you like it!

@endnode


